<h2 id=3D"section8"><span data-mce-fragment=3D"1">FAQ</span></h2>
<h3>What is the average OBP in Major League Baseball?</h3>
<p>The average OBP in Major League Baseball typically hovers around .320 to=
 .340, with variations depending on the era and specific seasons.</p>
<h3>Why is OBP considered more valuable than batting average?</h3>
<p>OBP is considered more valuable because it accounts for all ways a playe=
r can reach base, including walks and being hit by a pitch, providing a mor=
e comprehensive picture of offensive performance.</p>
<h3>How can I improve my OBP as a player?</h3>
<p>To improve your OBP, focus on developing your plate discipline to earn m=
ore walks, working on your hitting skills to increase your number of hits, =
